						               													<description>Kort p&amp;aring; kanten (&amp;quot;Card on the edge&amp;quot;) is a shameless party game in norwegian, where the purpose is to make funny, absurd and unfitting combinations of words, phrases, persons and situations.&amp;#10;To generalize, it's the norwegian version of Cards against humanity, with some new rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play begins with a judge, choosing a red question or fill-in-the-blank card from the top of the deck and showing it to all players. Each player holds a hand of ten white answer cards at the beginning of each round, and passes a card (sometimes two) to the judge, face-down, representing their answer to the question on the card. The judge determines which answer card(s) are funniest in the context of the question or fill-in-the-blank card. The player who submitted the chosen card(s) is given the question card to represent an point, and then the player to the left of the new judge becomes the judge for the next round. Play continues until the players agree to stop, at which point the player with the most points (red cards) is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition there are some new rules:&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Bestemor&amp;quot; (gradma) - draw an extra white card from the draw pile. If that card wins, agree on a punishment.&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Sidesprang&amp;quot; (side step) - before you read the white cards, draw another red card and use that instead.&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Kapitalisme&amp;quot; (capitalism) - discard one of the red point cards you have won to &amp;quot;punish&amp;quot; other players or switch 3 white cards.&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Folkestyre&amp;quot; (democracy) - Judges are stupid! Everone can vote. The card with most votes win!&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Samspill&amp;quot; (Interaction) - Too many players? Team up with more people on each team.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the publisher (translated):&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Kort p&amp;aring; kanten is distributed under a Creative Commons Attribution-Noncommercial-Share Alike 4.0 license - that means you can use and remix the game for free, but you can't sell it...&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
